.TH SL7-SENSORS 1 "July 2026" "sl7-sensors" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sl7-sensors \- ambient light / color sensor support for the Surface Laptop 7
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sl7-sensors
.IR command " [" args "]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
On Snapdragon X Elite laptops the ambient light sensor belongs to the
Qualcomm Sensor Core (SSC) on the ADSP, which reads its sensor
configuration from the host filesystem at runtime over FastRPC.
.B sl7-sensors
supplies that file service, a net.hadess.SensorProxy D-Bus daemon for
desktop auto-brightness, and command-line sensor readers.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup \fR[\fIwindows-root\fR]
One-time extraction of the sensor configuration from this machine's
Windows partition (root). With no argument, internal NTFS partitions are
scanned for a Windows installation.
.TP
.B lux
Stream the ambient light sensor to the terminal, one line per second.
.TP
.B color
Stream the color sensor: lux, correlated color temperature, chromaticity,
RGB and raw channels.
.TP
.B mode \fRcontroller|desktop
Choose who drives auto-brightness (root): this package's direct backlight
controller, or the desktop's own (GNOME/KDE) via the sensor proxy. Prints
the matching per-user
.BR gsettings (1)
command to run afterwards.
.TP
.B status
Show service states, the active mode and a current sensor reading.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/sl7-sensors/sns-config
Extracted sensor configuration served to the DSP.
.TP
.I /etc/default/sl7-sensor-proxy
Sensor proxy arguments; edited by
.BR "sl7-sensors mode" .
.TP
.I /var/lib/sl7-sensor-proxy/anchor.json
The direct controller's calibration anchor.
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation and caveats:
.I /usr/share/doc/sl7-sensors/README.md.gz
